<subSubSection id="C359FCF8FFCEFFEFFF549F7BFEF600DC" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFCAF73FFCEFFEFFF549F7BFB0203C3" blockId="4.[136,1452,263,685]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">
<emphasis id="B9377361FFCEFFEFFF549F7BFF280353" bold="true" box="[136,210,264,290]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C43D4F0FFCEFFEFFF009F7BFE8A0350" box="[220,368,263,290]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cassia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="selloi">
<emphasis id="B9377361FFCEFFEFFF009F7BFE8A0350" box="[220,368,263,290]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Cassia selloi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on the collection 
<emphasis id="B9377361FFCEFFEFFCE09F74FC420350" box="[828,952,263,289]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Sellow s.n.</emphasis>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F354EFE3FFCEFFEFFBD89F74FBB10350" box="[1028,1099,263,289]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, without any indication of the herbarium where the type was deposited. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2D282FFCEFFEFFD919F58FCA00337" author="Irwin, H. S. &amp; Barneby, R. C." box="[589,858,299,326]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" pagination="1 - 454" refId="ref5268" refString="Irwin, H. S. &amp; Barneby, R. C. (1982) The American Cassiinae: A synoptical revision of Leguminosae tribe Cassieae subtribe Cassiinae in the New World. Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 35: 1 - 454." type="journal article" year="1982">Irwin &amp; Barneby (1982)</bibRefCitation>
, in their revision of 
<taxonomicName id="4C43D4F0FFCEFFEFFBED9F5FFB8F0337" authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1754" box="[1073,1141,300,326]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Senna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9377361FFCEFFEFFBED9F5FFB8F0337" box="[1073,1141,300,326]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Senna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, suggested a specimen from Lambert’s personal herbarium as the 
<typeStatus id="54F811D1FFCEFFEFFDFA9F3CFD720318" box="[550,648,335,361]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis id="B9377361FFCEFFEFFD719F23FCEB0318" box="[685,785,335,362]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">
<taxonomicName id="4C43D4F0FFCEFFEFFD719F23FCF70318" box="[685,781,335,362]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cassia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="selloi">C. selloi</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2D282FFCEFFEFFC6A9F3CFBB5031B" author="Miller, H. H." box="[950,1103,335,362]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" pagination="489 - 553" refId="ref5500" refString="Miller, H. H. (1970) The herbarium of Aylmer Bourke Lambert notes on its acquisition, dispersal, and present whereabouts. Taxon 19: 489 - 553. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1218947" type="journal article" year="1970">Miller (1970)</bibRefCitation>
, George Don described several new species from the Lambert Herbarium, and after Lambert’s death, the collection was divided into approximately 317 lots, which are now deposited in at least 18 different institutions in Europe and the 
<collectingCountry id="F354EFE3FFCEFFEFFB879FE4FB0E03C3" box="[1115,1268,407,434]" name="United States of America" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">United States</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFCAF73FFCEFFEFFF619FCFFEF600DC" blockId="4.[136,1452,263,685]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">
Our research found 
<specimenCount id="9D4564FAFFCEFFEFFE459FC8FDCE03A4" box="[409,564,443,469]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" type="generic">six specimens</specimenCount>
referring to the collection 
<emphasis id="B9377361FFCEFFEFFC859FC8FC3303A4" box="[857,969,443,469]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">
<location id="8E9CF9A8FFCEFFEFFC859FC8FC5E03A4" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03EA1E65FFC9FFEFFF5499B4FEF600DC:8E9CF9A8FFCEFFEFFC859FC8FC5E03A4" box="[857,932,443,469]" country="Brazil" county="We" municipality="Wien Herbarium" name="Sellow" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Sellow</location>
s.n
</emphasis>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F354EFE3FFCEFFEFFBD79FC8FBB503A4" box="[1035,1103,443,469]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Brazil</collectingCountry>
deposited in different herbaria: 
<location id="8E9CF9A8FFCEFFEFFF549FACFE32038B" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03EA1E65FFC9FFEFFF5499B4FEF600DC:8E9CF9A8FFCEFFEFFF549FACFE32038B" box="[136,456,479,506]" country="Brazil" county="We" municipality="Wien Herbarium" name="Herbarium of Field Museum" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Herbarium of Field Museum</location>
(F, barcodes V0057681F and V0093913F), 
<location id="8E9CF9A8FFCEFFEFFC699FACFBD40388" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03EA1E65FFC9FFEFFF5499B4FEF600DC:8E9CF9A8FFCEFFEFFC699FACFBD40388" box="[949,1070,479,505]" country="Brazil" county="We" municipality="Wien Herbarium" name="Herbarium" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Herbarium</location>
Martin-Luther-Universität (
<collectionCode id="ED5237B6FFCEFFEFFAB59F93FA5D038B" box="[1385,1447,480,506]" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15866" name="Martin-Luther-Universität" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" type="Herbarium">HAL</collectionCode>
, barcode HAL0120725), 
<location id="8E9CF9A8FFCEFFEFFE7F9C70FDE6006C" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03EA1E65FFC9FFEFFF5499B4FEF600DC:8E9CF9A8FFCEFFEFFE7F9C70FDE6006C" box="[419,540,515,541]" country="Brazil" county="We" municipality="Wien Herbarium" name="Herbarium" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Herbarium</location>
of the 
<location id="8E9CF9A8FFCEFFEFFDAB9C70FC1C006F" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03EA1E65FFC9FFEFFF5499B4FEF600DC:8E9CF9A8FFCEFFEFFDAB9C70FC1C006F" box="[631,998,515,542]" country="Brazil" county="We" municipality="Wien Herbarium" name="Royal Botanic Gardens of Kew" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Royal Botanic Gardens of Kew</location>
(K, barcode K000555409), 
<location id="8E9CF9A8FFCEFFEFFAEE9C70FD8A0030" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03EA1E65FFC9FFEFFF5499B4FEF600DC:8E9CF9A8FFCEFFEFFAEE9C70FD8A0030" country="Brazil" county="We" municipality="Wien Herbarium" name="Herbarium of Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Herbarium of Muséum National d’Histoire Naturelle</location>
(P, barcode P00798381), and 
<collectingMunicipality id="6B983509FFCEFFEFFC029C54FB5A0030" box="[990,1184,551,577]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Wien Herbarium</collectingMunicipality>
(W-0028642). 
<collectingCounty id="629DD7FFFFCEFFEFFA8B9C5BFA860033" box="[1367,1404,552,578]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">We</collectingCounty>
are designating here the specimen deposited at P under barcode P00798381 as the 
<typeStatus id="54F811D1FFCEFFEFFBD99C38FB950014" box="[1029,1135,587,613]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">lectotype</typeStatus>
, as it is well preserved with leaves and flowers (characters used in the protologue), and has label annotations that coincide with those of the original description.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
